Shell Singapore Fire Caused by Maintenance Preparation, Today Says

-- B y   N e t t y   I d a y u   I s m a i l
-- 
2011-10-03T23:20:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/shell-singapore-fire-caused-by-maintenance-preparation-today-says.html
The fire at  Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSA) ’s
refinery at Pulau Bukom in  Singapore  was caused by preparation
work for maintenance, which included the draining of residual
oil in a pipeline, Today newspaper reported.   Preliminary findings from the Ministry of Manpower’s probe
into the fire showed the fire broke out at a pump house during
preparation work for maintenance, a spokesman at the ministry
was cited as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Netty Idayu Ismail in Singapore at 
